data.reddit:
Currently taking 112.5mg of Effexor XR (tapering down) and 10 mg of Prozac. 

Is this normal? Today I went to the ER due to horrible heart palpitations and shortness of breath. They checked my vitals and saw that my heart was beating really fast. I think my blood pressure was bit high too. 

I’m 24, 5’4, and 130 lbs. 

They ran some blood tests, chest x Ray, and ekg. The tests came out all fine. They put me on IV thinking I could be dehydrated to lower my heart rate. It did help a bit since I was resting but after I left the tachycardia continued so perhaps it didn’t make a difference. I was told to speak to my psychiatrist ASAP as well as my PCP.  

My boyfriend thinks it’s probably how I am reacting to the proZac and could be an anxiety symptom. Thing is I’m not feeling anxious it just came so suddenly. 

I just took 1mg of Ativan so it can help me relax and stop the palpitations. Well, I CAN still feel them. -_- so yep, there’s that. 

I’ve never reacted like that to antidepressants. 

Also I’d like to add that I need a root canal as well. I’ve been having lots of tooth pain and waiting for appointment. Currently taking Tylenol and ibuprofen here and there. I’m also a bit worried that I’m putting all that junk into my body that could be causing my heart to go into a funk.
